        Returns ``self`` shifted left by ``n`` coefficients by inserting
        zero coefficients. This is equivalent to multiplying the polynomial
        by x^n

            >>> R = fmpz_mod_poly_ctx(163)
            >>> f = R([1,2,3])
            >>> f.left_shift(0)
            3*x^2 + 2*x + 1
            >>> f.left_shift(1)
            3*x^3 + 2*x^2 + x
            >>> f.left_shift(4)
            3*x^6 + 2*x^5 + x^4

        """
